column21: Collaborative leaders can span the scope of your business by engaging people outside of their direct control and getting them to work as a team with a common goal. These groups get employees at all levels with a stake in the outcome. This strategy is more about facilitating the group effort than about making decisions for the group. In other words, a collaborative leader leads the group’s process, not the group itself.
